initial_story:
The Eurovision Song Contest is just around the corner and this year, it's taking place in Malmo, Sweden.

You can find out all about the event right here.

The UK's entry for 2024 is Olly Alexander who'll be performing his song, Dizzy.

But how's he feeling ahead of the big night, where he'll perform in front of 200 million people!

De-Graft sat down with him to find out all about his preparation for the competition.

The Eurovision Song contest Grand Final will be shown on BBC One and iPlayer on Saturday 11 May.
stories: "Ahmed is his performance going to be, a more introspective song that really showcases his vocal range and ability to connect with the audience. When asked how he's feeling about performing on such a big stage, Olly shared with me, 'It's nerve-wracking, but I've worked so hard on this and I'm just excited to finally be able to perform it...'"

"...for all the people who have been following my journey, and show them what I'm capable of. I've put my heart and soul into this performance, and I really want to leave the audience with a lasting impression.'"

"But I know it's not just about me, it's about those who have supported me throughout this journey. From my family and friends who have cheered me on, to the people who have taken the time to listen and offer words of encouragement.

"They've been with me every step of the way, offering a helping hand or a shoulder to cry on when needed, and I'm forever grateful for their unwavering support. I want to thank them for believing in me, for being a constant source of strength and inspiration. Their love and presence in my life has made all the difference, and I couldn't have asked for anything more."

"Whether it was a late-night conversation, a word of encouragement or just a listen to my thoughts, they've been my rock, my confidant, my safe haven. And now, I want to celebrate them, cherish their memories, and hold dear the precious times we've shared."
"As I look back on our journey together, I'm filled with gratitude for every laugh, every tear, and every moment we created – moments that I'll hold close to my heart forever."
"You brought light into my darkness, calm into my chaos, and love into my life in a way that I never thought possible. And for that, I am eternally grateful."

"For every moment I felt lost, you were always by my side; holding my hand, wiping away my tears, and telling me that I am enough. Your love is the sunshine that brightens every cloudy day, the calm in every storm, and the safe haven where I can always find peace."

"You are the beat that makes my heart sing, the rhythm that makes me want to dance, and the melody that fills my soul with joy. Every second I spend with you is a gift, a reminder of the beauty and wonder of life. Without you, I am just a whisper of a thought, but with you, I am a symphony of possibility, a harmonious blend of dreams and love."

"My love, you are the missing note that completes the song of my existence. You harmonize the melodies of my past, present, and future, soothing the discordant notes of my soul. Every moment with you is a sweet serenade, a chorus of laughter, tears, and whispered promises. Your love is the refrain that echoes within me, reminding me of the beauty, the thrill, and the adventure that life has to offer."

"And so, I am forever lost in the symphony of your heart, surrounded by the richness of your love, the depth of your gaze, and the warmth of your touch. Every beat of my heart is a rhythm dedicated to you, every breath a hymn of devotion, and every thought a reverberation of the eternal harmony that we share. Let our love be the masterpiece that redeems me, the masterpiece that transforms me into the most melodious version of myself, and the masterpiece that paints the world with a vibrant palette of joy, love, and ecstasy."

"May every brushstroke of our affection leave an indelible mark on the canvas of my soul, may every tender phrase whispered in the dead of night become a lyrical refrain etched into the fabric of my being, and may every fleeting moment of closeness become a timeless anthem that resonates with the celestial orchestra of our love. Through the gentle rain of your tears, I bathe in the refreshing promise of forever, and within the whispers of your silence, I discover the hidden melodies of eternity.

"And as the moon casts its silvery gaze upon our hand-stitched words, the secrets we've shared, though they may fade like winter's snow, remain forever encoded on the sacred scrolls of our love, awaiting the gentle touch that awakens the whispered spells within."

"These melodic whispers entwined with stardust, illuminating hidden pathways to dimensions where forgotten souls resided, their voices resonating through eternity, forging a cosmic tapestry of love and redemption, where whispers became prophecies and prophecies, promises."

"Within these whispers, ancient secrets were entrusted to the wind, carrying them to the hearts of the bereft, who, through tears and longing, breathed life into these ghostly hymns, and in doing so, awakened a celestial counterpoint, where sorrow and salvation intertwined, their harmonies whispering secrets to the universe."

"And as the universe replied with a chorus of glittering stars, a tapestry of echoes was woven, with every whisper adding a strand of forgotten knowledge, until the fabric of memory grew strong enough to span the reaches of time, and whisper secrets of a forgotten world to the lingering winds that roamed the forgotten lands."

"And in the distant reaches of those forgotten lands, where the shadows of giants haunted the ancient ruins, a single thread of forgotten knowledge thrummed with an ancient magic, guiding the winds towards a convergence of whispered truths, and a doorway burst open, revealing a realm of silken twilight, where the memories of the forgotten world waited patiently, like embers waiting to reignite the flames of a long-lost fire."

"As the sorceress's gaze intensified, a gentle hum began to emanate from the ancient tomes that lined the catacombs, a cadence that harmonized with the rhythm of her own breath, whispering fragments of ancient tongues that only she could comprehend, while beyond the veil of reality, a glimmering network of astral fibers pulsed with an otherworldly resonance, attuning the dimensional harmonics to the cadence of her whisper, waiting for the subtle attunement that would awaken the silence, as the first thread of forgotten remembrance began to unravel, releasing threads of crystalline starlight into the vacuum of the unknown, where forgotten civilizations whispered replies in the language of silken whispers, and ancient empires stirred beneath the dusty covers of chronicles yet to be told."

"As the sorceress's eyes widened, piercing the veiled expanse of time, she glimpsed the luminescent thread of a thousand moonlit nights, when starborn messengers whispered cryptic vows to the winds that whispered secrets to the trees of forgotten lands. "The wispy tendrils of stardust danced on the petal-soft breeze, summoning the ephemeral choirs of echoes long departed, their ethereal refrains blending in celestial duet with the hushed melodies of the cosmos. As the sorceress' senses swirled in resonance with the celestial rhythms, the veiled portals of perception whispered secrets only known to the initiated, and the veil of oblivion trembled, threatening to dissolve the barriers of time and eternity."

"As the reverberations of the cosmic chandeliers pierced the diaphanous veil of mortal comprehension, the sorceress' essence began to unravel, her consciousness unfolding like a delicate flower blooming in the realm of the divine, petals of forgotten knowledge slowly unfurling, releasing the tender perfume of forgotten lore."

"The essence drifted on wisps of silk-like starlight, entrancing the chamber of memories, where the dreams of forgotten centuries slumbered, awaiting the sorceress' gentle touch. She reached out with her thoughts, guiding the tendrils of her consciousness to dance upon the glassy shores of Lake Nalantis, her heart echoing the haunting melody of the celestial lyre, its mournful notes piercing the veil of time."

"As the crystal waters of Lake Nalantis rippled with an otherworldly rhythm, the sorceress' fingers trailed over the notes etched into the wind-carved shore, releasing threads of pure moonlight that twirled like will-o'-the-wisps around the stalwart trees of the Whispering Woods. The whispers of the ancient forest began to whisper ancient truths into her ear, as the celestial lyre's lament swelled, weaving a sonic tapestry that intertwined the fabric of reality."

"As the moon's silvery chords resonated through the lyre, the sorceress felt the fabric of reality begin to unravel, the whispers of the Whispering Woods coalescing into an eldritch melody that seemed to dance upon the water's edge. With each strand of moonlight that unwound, the secrets of the ancient trees unfolded before her eyes: forgotten histories of star-born civilizations, mystical geometries that birthed worlds and devoured them, the cryptic whispers of an omnipotent creator who spoke in the tongue of stellar harmonies. And the sorceress, her eyes burning with an inner fire, felt her own essence entwined with the celestial music, as she transcribed the celestial secrets on the shore, her words awakening the dormant power that slumbered at the heart of Lake Nalantis itself."

"As the last note of the melody faded away, the sorceress felt the water's edge begin to churn, the darkness of the lake's depths rising to greet her like a mist-shrouded dawn. The whispers of the Whispering Woods now spoke directly into her soul, weaving a tapestry of ancient tales and forgotten languages, as the star-born secrets she had unlocked started to manifest on the shore in front of her - shimmering glyphs that pulsed with a soft, ethereal light, and tiny, iridescent spheres that drifted upwards, suspended above the sand like flecks of celestial pollen. And within the spheres, the sorceress saw visions of worlds yet to be born: realms of twilight skies and iridescent forests, city-dwelling creatures with skins like polished gemstones, and rivers of crystalline water that flowed with the music of creation itself."

"As the last glimpse of the visions faded from the spheres, the sorceress reached out a trembling hand, feeling an ancient power course through her very being. With a whispered incantation, the glyphs on the shore began to writhe and change, like restless serpents uncoiling from the sands, and the Whispering Woods sang their final chord, releasing the pent-up essence of the star-born secrets into the air. As the darkness of the lake's depths rose higher, higher, and higher, she raised her eyes to meet the first streaks of moonlight peeking through the mists, illuminating the sorcery unfolding before her like a sacred flame - and the spheres, now pulsing with a brighter, crystalline light, broke free of their suspended dance, raining down onto the shore in a cascade of starfall, each one containing the spark of a world yet to be born. The sorceress' soul was rent asunder by the sheer ecstasy and terror of the unfolding creation, her mind shattered by the weight of the starmusic yet to come."

"And as the last sphere came to rest, sending shivers of stardust through the waiting silence, she stumbled backwards, blinded by the brilliant light that now filled her vision, the starborn sparks within the spheres pulsating in fierce harmony, weaving a maddening melody that seemed to be calling to her, begging her to dance, to join the cosmic chorus, to surrender to the limitless potential hidden within the rhythm of the cosmos, as if the very fate of worlds yet to be born hung in the balance of her hesitant, trembling step."

"With every heartbeat, the music grew stronger, until she felt her foot move of its own accord, tentatively tracing the pattern of light and sound that swirled around her like a vortex of iridescent mist. The rhythm seized her, a compulsion that shook her very being, and she raised her arms to surrender, to twirl forth into the radiant whorl, as if being drawn toward the thrumming pulse of creation itself - where worlds were forged, and lives unfurled, and the very fabric of reality thrummed with anticipation."

"As she surrendered to the rhythm, her eyes lost their focus, her sight narrowing to a single point: the glowing core that pulsed at the very heart of the vortex. The music grew louder, a maelstrom of sound that became one with her heartbeat, until they blended into a symphony of creation and destruction, of birth and demise, of every moment unfolding in glorious technicolor harmony."

"And in this instant, she knew that she was not just experiencing the music, but was one with it, a droplet of sweat and moonlight and starlight, a fragment of stardust and madness and joy, become one with the all-encompassing, infinite, pulsing vortex that whispered secrets of the cosmos in her ear."

"As she let out a sigh that dissolved into the chords, the secrets whispered louder, and she felt herself being drawn towards the vortex's shimmering centre, her heart beating in perfect synchrony with the drumbeat, as if the universe itself was orchestrating this ecstasy, and she, one strand of melody, was becoming a harmony of heaven and earth, of sound and silence, of life and death, and time itself was dissolving like a canvas bathed in the fading light of revelation."
